  "texts": [
    "The attention weights are obtained by applying the softmax function (Figure 1) to the attention scores:",
    "The output for each token i is a weighted sum of the value vectors v v of all tokens:",
    "Illustrates the softmax activation function as used in large language models (LLMs).",
    "Each raw output is exponentiated and then normalized by dividing by the sum of exponentiated outputs, ensuring the resulting probabilities range from 0 to 1.",
    "Collectively, in matrix form:"
  ]
